               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Yasay “Vita of Yasay” (fols. 3ra-29vb)
 
 Additiones
                     1-3.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The Gadla Yasay is still an unpublished text.</note>
                     <note>- On <locus target="#29va">29va</locus> ls.1-2, the 9th of Maskaram is
                        mentioned as the dies natalis of ʾabbā Yasay.</note>
                     <note>- On <locus target="#29va">29va</locus>, the text ends with a subscriptio
                        (ለዘ፡ አጽሐፎ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ወልደ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለዘአንበቦ፡ ወለጸሐፎ፡ ኅቡረ፡ … ይምሐሮሙ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡…)
                        which is a supplication for the commissioner of the Ms., Walda Māryām, and
                        for the reader, the scribe, the translator and the one who have listened to
                        its story.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
