               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0100DAY">Dǝrba Dabra ʾAbuna Yasay /DAY</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1910" notAfter="1911">1903 A.M. (= 1910 A.D.)
 The
                        date 1903 A.M. and the time of Mark the Evangelist (= 1910 A.D., cp. ChChron
                        172) are mentioned in Additio 3 as the time when the Ms. was commissioned by
                        daǧǧāzmāč Gugsa.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>daǧǧāzmāč Gugsa (baptismal name Walda Māryām)
                     of ʾAgʷǝʾdi, Hangʷäda (s. Ḥangoda Dabra Mǝḥrat Qǝddus Mikāʾel), is mentioned as
                     the commissioner of the Ms. in Additiones 2 and 3 and in the supplication at
                     the end of the text (29va-b).</provenance></history>
